The differential measures of each alternative are aggregated to get its collective differential measure. Then, using the score function (10), the CDFMs are defuzzified to get the total degree of superiority of the ideal ratings to the ratings of the alternatives for the evaluation criteria. Then, the alternatives are ranked in ascending order as given in Table 4. From Table 4, the final rank is A3>A1>A2>A4>A5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${A}_{3}>{A}_{1}>{A}_{2}>{A}_{4}>{A}_{5}$$\end{document}.Table 4
